HEADWORD: pathologist
<hw>pa*thol"o*gist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pathologiste</ets>.]</ety> <def>One skilled in pathology; an
investigator in pathology; <as>as, the <ex>pathologist</ex> of a
hospital, whose duty it is to determine the causes of the
diseases</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
